The paper deals with the construction of nearly optimal eps-nets for convex bodies, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithmic techniques used involve lattice coverings and enumeration, which are also relevant to discrete and computational geometry (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of sparsification and densification techniques, which are commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents an application to volume estimation, which is a problem in computational complexity (cs.CC).
